At least 20 people were left injured late last, including several children following a collision between two taxis at the Simon Vermooten and Pretoria Road intersection in Silverton, Pretoria. On arrival at the scene, paramedics found the two taxis on the side of the road. ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said, “according to the paramedics several people were found seated inside the vehicles while others were found walking around on the scene”. Meiring added that it was also found that the patients had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate. The local authorities were on the scene to investigate the cause of the collision. -TNA Reporter 